set.seed(1)
x=matrix(rnorm(20*2),ncol=2)
y=c(rep(-1,10),rep(1,10))
x[y==1,]=x[y==1,]+1
plot(x,col=(3-y))

dat=data.frame(x=x, y=as.factor (y))
library (e1071)
svmfit =svm(y~., data=dat , kernel ="linear", cost =0.1,scale =FALSE )
summary(svmfit)

normal svm test, when we change the kenal the curve changes

this test we have used the data phoneme in fda.usc; Elements of phoneme: ..$learn: learning sample of curves. fdata class object with: i.- “data”: Matrix of class fdata with 250 curves (rows) discretized in 150 points or argvals (columns). , ii.- “argvals”, iii.- “rangeval”: range(“argvals”), iv.- “names” list with: main an overall title “Phoneme learn”, xlab title for x axis “frequencies” and ylab title for y axis “log-periodograms”.

..$test: testing sample of curves. fdata class object with: i.- “data”: Matrix of class fdata with 250 curves (rows) discretized in 150 points or argvals (columns). , ii.- “argvals”, iii.- “rangeval”: range(“argvals”), iv.- “names” list with: main an overall title “Phoneme learn”, xlab title for x axis “frequencies” and ylab title for y axis “log-periodograms”.

..$classlearn:learning class numbers (as factor). Factor levels: “sh” 1, “iy” 2, “dcl” 3, “aa” 4 and “ao” 5.

..$classtest: testing class numbers (as factor). Factor levels: “sh” 1, “iy” 2, “dcl” 3, “aa” 4 and “ao” 5.

data(phoneme)
mlearn<-phoneme[["learn"]]

mtest<-phoneme[["test"]]
gtest<-phoneme[["classtest"]]

here we compared the diffirent parametters Weights: • if character string =‘equal’ same weights for each observation (by default) and =‘inverse’ for inverse-probability of weighting. • if numeric vector of length n, Weight values of each observation

If type is“1vsall” (by default) a maximum probability scheme is applied: requires G binary classifiers. If type is “majority” (only for multicalss classification G > 2) a voting scheme is applied: requires G (G - 1) / 2 binary classifiers

laplace value used for Laplace smoothing (additive smoothing). Defaults to 0 (no Laplace smoothing)
